{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Grease and line base and sides of a spring form cake tin (20 cm) with baking paper.","Place butter, sugar and yoghurt in mixing bowl then cream <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add lemon zest, salt, baking powder, ground almonds, polenta and lemon juice then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add eggs and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add diced strawberries and nectarines then mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 3.5<b>. Transfer batter to prepared tin and smooth surface. Arrange fruit slices on top then bake for 1 hour 15 minutes (170°C) or until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean, covering with foil if top of cake becomes too brown. Leave to cool for 10 minutes then remove from tin and allow to cool on a wire rack.","Serve slightly warm with crème fraîche."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["125 g butter, diced, plus extra for greasing","250 g light brown sugar","60 g Greek yoghurt","1 lemon, zest and 30 g juice","½ tsp fine sea salt","1 tsp baking powder","200 g ground almonds","200 g polenta","3 medium eggs","100 g fresh strawberries, hulled, 50 g diced (0.5 cm), 50 g finely sliced","100 g nectarines, stoned, 50 g diced (0.5 cm), 50 g finely sliced","150 g crème fraîche, to serve"]}],"id":"r122642","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-qiWSLs8bMD8\/XZWrJV3Ud6I\/AAAAAAAAfi0\/FXcjGrbDV-0wXFxQRCpp_ClREoMctoiugCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ckDzrMptccLVfGy-.png","title":"Strawberry and Nectarine Polenta and Almond Cake","publishedAt":"2017-06-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11.8 g","fat":"38.8 g","uom":"per 8 portion","carbohydrates":"56.6 g","calories":"2605 kJ \/ 623 kcal"},"usefulItems":"spring form tin (Ø 20 cm), baking paper, wire rack, aluminium foil, oven","basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 45m","8 portions"]}